UID:86454-1772969400-1772974800@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Celebrating Women Composers
DESCRIPTION:Sthree Thaal Tharang is a soulful celebration of women in music. \nThe repertoire draws from the vachanas of Akkamahadevi\, addressed to Chenna Mallikarjuna and marked by spiritual intensity and metaphysical longing; the verses of Andal\, whose poetic imagination and theological vision shaped Tamil bhakti literature; and the bhajans of Mirabai\, whose devotion was fearless\, deeply personal\, and entirely her own. \nThe programme moves into the twentieth century through Ambujam Krishna\, whose lyrical clarity and devotional depth brought a different kind of rigour to the form\, and through compositions popularised by pioneering women performers whose interpretations shaped modern concert practice. The morning culminates in laya-oriented compositions by Sukanya Ramgopal\, where ghata tharang meets percussive texture and melodic interplay. \nSthree Thaal Tharang situates women not at the margins but at the centre of music’s evolving history: composers\, interpreters\, and custodians of a living tradition. \nSupported by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/women-composers-in-classical-music/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Gender,Heritage,Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_WCICM.jpg
END:VEVENT
