SUMMARY:The Long Game: Opportunity\, Excellence and Institutional Power
DESCRIPTION:Opportunity is abundant. Outcomes\, however\, are strategic.  \nThe four women on this panel have navigated all of it. Venture capital and enterprise strategy. Global talent transformation. The slow\, necessary work of making the technology industry legible to the women coming up behind them. Startups built from scratch and careers that kept becoming something new.  \nThey have done this inside institutions that weren’t built for them\, in markets that moved before they were ready\, in moments that required a decision before the picture was clear. Together they examine how signals and opportunities are recognised\, and sometimes missed. How excellence is sustained over decades\, not just built in a moment. How to navigate boards\, capital\, and institutions. How and when to seek help from the mentors\, sponsors\, and allies who make the difference.  \nThe answers come from lived experience. The lessons\, hard-won as they are\, turn out to be universal. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-long-game-opportunity-excellence-and-institutional-power/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Development,Science,Society,Technology
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-18-3.jpg
END:VEVENT
