SUMMARY:Her Labour\, Her Law
DESCRIPTION:\nThis session is in English and Kannada. \nDomestic work keeps the country running. But the women who make it possible\, often after tending to their own homes first\, have no contracts\, no fixed hours\, and no legal protection. \nThe proposed Domestic Workers Bill in Karnataka aims to regulate the industry\, bringing in protections enjoyed by employees in the formal sector. This panel examines what the Bill actually means: for the women it seeks to protect\, for the households that depend on them\, and for a labour movement that has long treated domestic work as an afterthought. \nA Q&A with the audience will follow. \nThis event is a part of our programming to celebrate International Women’s Day. Music\, theatre\, and conversation: by women\, for everyone. \n\n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/her-labour-her-law/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Development,Gender,Law
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-17-2.jpg
END:VEVENT
